    "slug": "danab-commandos-seize-long-held-al-shabaab-base-near-jilib",
    "summary": "Somali Danab forces and Jubaland troops captured the Dambase area near Jilib, a key Al-Shabaab stronghold held for over a decade. The operation marks the first time government forces have entered the area in 15 years.",
    "content": "Elite Somali Danab commandos, alongside Jubaland regional security forces, have taken control of the Dambase area on the outskirts of Jilib district, a militant stronghold that had been under Al-Shabaab control for more than 15 years. The operation, which began early this week, targeted a key base used by the group to orchestrate attacks across southern Somalia. The seizure represents a significant setback for Al-Shabaab's operational capabilities in the Middle Jubba region.\n\nJilib, located approximately 100 kilometers north of Kismayo, has long been a strategic hub for Al-Shabaab, providing access to key supply routes and serving as a staging ground for offensives against government and African Union forces. The Dambase area, a heavily fortified camp, was used for training fighters and storing weapons. Intelligence reports indicated that the base was pivotal in coordinating attacks on convoys and towns in the region.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, especially those with roots in Jubaland, this development signals renewed efforts to dismantle Al-Shabaab's strongholds. Many diaspora families have been affected by instability in the region, and the capture of Dambase could pave the way for improved security and economic recovery in areas long cut off from development. The operation also highlights the growing effectiveness of Somali-led security initiatives with support from international partners.\n\nResidents in nearby towns have reported a sense of cautious optimism, though concerns remain about potential retaliation from the militant group. The advancing forces are now conducting clearance operations to destroy improvised explosive devices and booby-trapped structures left behind by retreating fighters. Commanders have urged civilians to avoid the area until it is fully secured.\n\nThe capture of this stronghold comes amid a broader campaign by Somali security forces to reclaim territory ahead of expected offensives during the upcoming dry season. Analysts note that sustained control of such areas will require continued military pressure and efforts to establish governance and services to prevent the group from regaining a foothold.\n\nRead the original report from Radio Dalsan here: https://radiodalsan.com/2026/07/18/danab-forces-overrun-al-shabaab-stronghold-near-jilib/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=danab-forces-overrun-al-shabaab-stronghold-near-jilib",
