    "slug": "somalia-regional-lawmaker-fahima-qooje-resigns-flips-allegiance-to-somaliland",
    "summary": "Fahima Qooje, a prominent figure in the 2023 Dhulbahante uprising, has resigned from Somalia's Federal State of Somalia and declared her return to Somaliland, renouncing the goal of a unified Somalia.",
    "content": "Fahima Qooje, who served as a lawmaker in Somalia's newest federal member state, has announced her resignation and decision to rejoin Somaliland. The move marks a significant political shift for Qooje, who was a vocal figure in the 2023 Dhulbahante rebellion against Somaliland's control over the Sool and Togdheer regions.\n\nIn a statement made on Friday, Qooje said she had abandoned the idea of Greater Somalia and was realigning with Somaliland. Her reversal is notable given her previous prominence as a civilian representative in the opposition movement, which sought to challenge Somaliland's authority in disputed territories.\n\nThe decision has drawn attention due to Qooje's influential role in the conflict over Sool and Togdheer, areas that have been a flashpoint between Somalia and Somaliland. Her resignation from the regional parliament signals a fracturing of political cohesion within the federal state, which has been attempting to consolidate control since its establishment.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, Qooje's defection underscores the enduring complexities of Somali political identity. Many Somalis abroad maintain ties to both sides of the Somalia-Somaliland divide, and her reversal may influence diaspora perceptions of state legitimacy and unity.\n\nThe development also highlights the volatility of regional alliances in the Horn of Africa, as shifting individual loyalties can impact broader political dynamics. Observers are monitoring whether other figures will follow Qooje's lead, potentially altering the balance of power in the disputed regions.\n\nRead the original report from Somalia Guardian here: https://www.somaliguardian.com/news/somalia-news/somalia-regional-lawmaker-fahima-qooje-rejoins-somaliland/",
